WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.000
[Unknown]: I.V.M.

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:06.000
[Amit Varma]: The internet is amazing, isn't it?

00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:08.000
[Amit Varma]: When I first began to explore the internet,

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:10.000
[Amit Varma]: more than 20 years ago,

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:12.000
[Amit Varma]: I was blown away by the possibilities.

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:14.000
[Amit Varma]: I thought, wow, this is going to do so much

00:00:14.000 --> 00:00:16.000
[Amit Varma]: to help people express themselves

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:18.000
[Amit Varma]: and to help people communicate with each other.

00:00:18.000 --> 00:00:20.000
[Amit Varma]: The internet put the tools of publishing

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:22.000
[Amit Varma]: into the hands of every individual.

00:00:22.000 --> 00:00:24.000
[Amit Varma]: Anyone, with a little effort,

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:26.000
[Amit Varma]: could start a webpage of her own.

00:00:26.000 --> 00:00:28.000
[Amit Varma]: With even less effort, one could start a blog.

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:30.000
[Amit Varma]: And as time went by, with almost no effort at all,

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:32.000
[Amit Varma]: we could write posts about our lives

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:34.000
[Amit Varma]: that all our friends could read.

00:00:34.000 --> 00:00:36.000
[Amit Varma]: We could broadcast our thoughts to the world,

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:38.000
[Amit Varma]: 140 characters at a time.

00:00:38.000 --> 00:00:40.000
[Amit Varma]: We could post pictures and videos

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:42.000
[Amit Varma]: and comment on the pictures and videos of others

00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:44.000
[Amit Varma]: and discover ourselves and the world around us

00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:46.000
[Amit Varma]: as distinctions of geography

00:00:46.000 --> 00:00:48.000
[Amit Varma]: and race and class

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:50.000
[Amit Varma]: and even language would cease to matter.

00:00:50.000 --> 00:00:52.000
[Amit Varma]: At the least, because of the internet,

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:54.000
[Amit Varma]: human beings would talk to each other

00:00:54.000 --> 00:00:56.000
[Amit Varma]: much more than they ever did before.

00:00:56.000 --> 00:00:58.000
[Amit Varma]: That's what I thought then.

00:00:58.000 --> 00:01:00.000
[Amit Varma]: But, alas, it hasn't quite

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:02.000
[Amit Varma]: worked out that way.

00:01:02.000 --> 00:01:04.000
[Amit Varma]: One of the big lessons of our modern age is this.

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:06.000
[Amit Varma]: We may all talk a lot

00:01:06.000 --> 00:01:08.000
[Amit Varma]: at the same time,

00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:10.000
[Amit Varma]: but no one really listens anymore.

